:: Introduction {"position":"325,400","size":"100,100"}
Hello and welcome to our interview with the creator of the Truman show. How are you doing today?

[[Good->Question 1]]
[[Busy, but we'll get through it ->Question 1]]


:: Not Possible {"position":"825,250","size":"100,100"}
High Ratings, High Sponsors, Truman Finds Out


:: Question 1 {"position":"325,525","size":"100,100"}
The Truman Show is a world wide phenomenon, with fans from around the globe. Did you ever expect it to get this big?

[[Yes, when I came up with the idea of having a main actor who has no idea he is in a show, I knew it would be a huge success. ->Question 2]]

[[No, I could have never seen this amount of success. ->Question 2]]


:: Question 2 {"position":"325,650","size":"100,100"}
How do you keep this show running 24 hours a day, 365 days a year?

[[Well, having sponsorships placed around the world help us out a lot and make it so we don't have to run commercials. ->Question 3]]

[[That's a little industry secret, and a lot of hard work. ->Question 3]]


:: Question 3 {"position":"325,775","size":"100,100"}
Have you ever had any concerns about having a person be trapped in a TV show set, not knowing what the rest of reality is like?

[[No, of course not. He is living a life most of us would die for. ->Interuption]]

[[*No Comment* ->Interuption]]


